// @run
// @log OTHER
// MAP-THROUGH-CLOSURE-RESULT in a union arm, the PURE spelling — the R2×R1 combo
// (rep-fuzz `p1r (() => {[string]: f64}) | {w: i32}`). The union annotation is the
// program's ONLY map mention (the caller passes only the decoy arm, so no
// `{[string]: f64}` binding annotation ever forces the map machinery): the whole
// spelling is ONE TypeRef whose closure-arm RESULT map every branch of the
// `collectA` scan missed, so the narrowed call-result map ops rejected "map type
// not collected" even though the arm's result names a map.
// `forceCloResultMapTypes` now forces the shared map machinery + interns the
// result's value slot from the arm (nullable-closure and curried spellings ride the
// same walk); the arm's sig was already keyed (`unionArmSigKey`, the #910
// discipline) and the call-result's shape resolves through the checker's recorded
// map type (`mapShapeOfExpr`'s Call fallback). The live-closure spelling (a real
// map constructed elsewhere) is pinned by
// `tests/cases/maps/closure-field-variant-map-result.vl`; this one pins that the
// narrowed branch COMPILES — and stays dead-correct — with no other map in sight.
function useIt(p: (() => {[string]: f64}) | {w: i32}) {
  const t0 = p
  if t0 is () => {[string]: f64} {
    const t1 = t0()["k"] ?? 14.5
    print(t1)
  } else {
    print("OTHER")
  }
}

function go() {
  useIt({w: 77})
}
go()
